# Security Rules

## Secrets & credentials

- NEVER commit `.env*`, API keys, tokens, passwords, or Firebase config overrides to git.
- Put personal/local credentials in `.env.local` or `.env.development.local` (gitignored).
- If you see a secret in code, flag it immediately — do not proceed.

## User data

- Collaboration data is end-to-end encrypted. Do not weaken or bypass encryption in `excalidraw-app/collab/`.
- Do not log or expose user scene data, file contents, or room keys to console in production builds.

## Dependencies

- Do not add new npm packages without explicit approval.
- Before using a new dependency, check for known vulnerabilities (`yarn audit` or equivalent).
- Prefer well-maintained packages with active security patching.

## Input handling

- Sanitize URLs before rendering (the project already uses `@braintree/sanitize-url`; use it).
- Do not use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` or `eval()`.
- Validate imported `.excalidraw` JSON before restoring (restore.ts handles this — do not bypass it).

## How to verify

1. `rg -in "api.key|secret|token|password" --glob "!.env*" --glob "!node_modules" --glob "!yarn.lock"` — should return zero real secrets.
2. `rg -n "dangerouslySetInnerHTML|eval(" packages/ excalidraw-app/` — should return zero results (or only safe/approved usages).
3. Confirm `.env.local` and `.env.development.local` are in `.gitignore`.
